# Pre-push: full Next.js build + type check.
#
# Catches the failure modes pre-commit's lint-only check misses:
#   - webpack module resolution (e.g. `@sparticuz/chromium` missing from
#     PLAYHUB's deps when imported from shared veo/auth.ts — bit us
#     2026-05-17, took 2 deploy iterations to spot remotely)
#   - tsc errors that lint doesn't surface
#   - Next.js route-level type-check (.next/types/* — bit us 2026-05-17
#     when a deleted /api/veo/invite route left stale type files)
#
# `next build` runs lint + type-check + production compile in one shot,
# so this is the same gate Netlify enforces — just locally, before the
# remote build burns ~60-90s of CI minutes.
#
# Skipped: vitest (run separately, slower, often async-with-real-services).
# Run `npm run release` manually for the full pre-release sweep.
#
# Emergency bypass: `git push --no-verify` — but flag it loudly and
# expect to clean up the broken Netlify build manually.
npm run build
